<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,303,773,799]" box="[189,303,773,799]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,773,799]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,773,799]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1399,819,951]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
The coloration of the legs of Middle East specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Remm" authorityYear="1974" box="[827,1037,819,845]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachypyga">
<emphasis box="[827,1037,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Bezzia pachypyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is highly variable and different from that in the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Remm H." box="[673,844,854,881]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="429 - 442" refId="ref14969" refString="Remm H. 1974. A review of species of the genus Bezzia Kieffer (Diptera, Ceratopogonidae) from the fauna of the USSR. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie 53: 429 - 442." type="journal article" year="1974">Remm (1974)</bibRefCitation>
. However, diagnostic characters of the highly complicated male genitalia match the original descriptions of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Remm" authorityYear="1974" box="[943,1107,889,915]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachypyga">
<emphasis box="[943,1107,889,915]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B. pachypyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its junior synonym 
<taxonomicName authority="Boorman &amp; van Harten, 2002" authorityName="Boorman &amp; van Harten" authorityYear="2002" box="[189,706,925,951]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="omanensis">
<emphasis box="[189,346,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B. omanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Boorman J. &amp; van Harten A." box="[353,706,925,951]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="427 - 462" refId="ref13709" refString="Boorman J. &amp; van Harten A. 2002. Some Ceratopogonidae (Insecta: Diptera) from the Arabian Peninsula, with particular reference to the Republic of Yemen. Fauna of Arabia 19: 427 - 462." type="journal article" year="2002">Boorman &amp; van Harten, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
